So to directly answer — a normal View just saves me from writing repetitive SQL and helps with security/abstraction, it does NOT make queries faster on its own, since it re-runs the same query underneath every time.
Only an Indexed or Materialized View actually improves performance, because it physically stores the precomputed result instead of recalculating it every time


What is CTE?
Yes, exactly right — a CTE, or Common Table Expression, is used to break down a large, complex query into smaller, more readable, named parts. Instead of writing deeply nested subqueries, 
