what is normalisation?
Normalization is the process of organizing data in a database to reduce redundancy and improve data integrity. It involves breaking down a large table into smaller, related tables, and defining 
relationships between them using Foreign Keys — so that the same piece of data isn't unnecessarily duplicated across multiple rows.


What are Transactions?
A Transaction is a group of one or more SQL operations that are executed together as a single unit of work — either ALL of them succeed and get saved, or if any one fails,
ALL of them get rolled back, leaving the database unchanged. This ensures data stays consistent, especially in operations involving multiple related steps.


